None of these conditions are constant. They can all vary based on the value of `a`:

```JavaScript
// The condition will be true if `a = [1]` but false if `a = []`
if(`${[...a]}`) {
  //
};

// The condition will be true if `a = "1"` but false if `a = ""`
if(`${[{toString: () => a}]}`) {
  //
};

// The condition will be true if `a = "1"` but false if `a = ""`
if("" + {toString: () => a}) {
  //
}

// The condition will be true if `a = "1"` but false if `a = ""`
if("" + [{toString: () => a}]) {
  //
};

// The condition will be true if `a = "1"` but false if `a = "0"`  or `a = ""`
if(+[{toString: () => a}]) {
  //
};
```
